-- Chilean Stocks: Embotelladora Andina, IAM and Sigdo Koppers
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-04-02T19:41:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/chilean-stocks-andina-corpbanca-iam-sigdo-koppers-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa index  increased 0.5 percent to 4,694.86. The  MSCI
Chile index  advanced 1.5 percent to 2,695.95.  Embotelladora Andina SA (AKO/A)   climbed 1.7 percent to
a record 2,788.7 pesos.  Chile ’s largest Coca-Cola bottler signed
a binding contract to take over Embotelladora  Coca-Cola Polar (KOPOLAR)  SA
in an all-stock transaction agreed to by the two companies’
controllers in February, according to regulatory filings posted
March 30 on the securities regulator’s website.  Inversiones Aguas Metropolitanas SA (IAM)   fell 0.6
percent to 820 pesos for the biggest drop in almost five weeks.
The Chilean holding company that owns a controlling stake in
 Aguas Andinas SA (AGUAS/A) , Chile’s largest water utility, had its
recommendation cut to hold from buy at Banco Santander SA.  Sigdo Koppers SA (SK)   gained 2.8 percent to 1,157 pesos,
its highest price since January 2011. The Santiago-based
industrial holding company said in a March 30 statement that it
joined with Breca, a unit of  Peru ’s Brescia Group, to buy
Brazilian explosives company IBQ Industrias Quimicas for $120
million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
